Magic

  • Random sample
    • 100 people
    • another 100 people
    • chances are the means are very different
    • how about 1000 people?
    • less different
    • means of these samples are normally distributed with standard deviation of:
      • \(\sqrt \frac{p*(1 -p)}{n}\)
      • maximize this given \(n\)
      • also called the standard error
